# Authentication & Permissions System

The application uses **NextAuth.js v5** with **Supabase** for authentication and a custom role-based permission system.

## Authentication Setup

### Provider Configuration
- **File**: [src/components/auth-provider.tsx](mdc:src/components/auth-provider.tsx)
- Uses `SessionProvider` from NextAuth.js
- Configured for development localhost URLs
- Handles session management and token refresh

### NextAuth Configuration
- **File**: [src/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts](mdc:src/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts)
- Integrates with Supabase using `@auth/supabase-adapter`
- Handles OAuth providers and session management

## Role-Based Permission System

### User Roles
Defined in [src/lib/permissions.ts](mdc:src/lib/permissions.ts):

```typescript
export type UserRole = 'student' | 'teacher' | 'admin'
```

### Role Assignment
Roles are determined by **email address** using predefined lists:

```typescript
// Admin emails (full access)
export const ADMIN_EMAILS = [
  'antoccic@fitchburg.k12.ma.us',
  'craigantocci@gmail.com'
]

// Teacher emails (includes all admin emails)
export const TEACHER_EMAILS = [
  ...ADMIN_EMAILS,
  // Add teacher-only emails here
]
```

### Permission Matrix

| Permission | Student | Teacher | Admin |
|------------|---------|---------|-------|
| View Lessons | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| View Assignments | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Create Assignments | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Manage Assignments | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Access Admin Panel | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| Create Lessons | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |

### Permission Checking

```typescript
// Get user role
const role = getUserRole(session?.user?.email)

// Check specific permission
const canCreate = hasPermission(email, 'canCreateAssignments')

// Get all permissions for role
const permissions = getUserPermissions(role)
```

## Authentication Patterns

### Session Access
```typescript
import { useSession } from 'next-auth/react'

const { data: session, status } = useSession()
const userRole = getUserRole(session?.user?.email)
```

### API Route Protection
```typescript
import { auth } from '@/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route'

const session = await auth()
if (!session?.user?.id) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 })
}

// Role-based access
const userRole = session.user?.role || 'student'
if (userRole !== 'admin' && userRole !== 'teacher') {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Forbidden' }, { status: 403 })
}
```

### Component-Level Protection
```typescript
import { getUserRole } from '@/lib/permissions'

const userRole = getUserRole(session?.user?.email)
const canAccessQuestionBank = userRole === 'admin' || userRole === 'teacher'

if (!canAccessQuestionBank) {
  return <div>Access denied</div>
}
```

## Context Integration

### Question Bank Access
The [QuestionBankContext](mdc:src/contexts/QuestionBankContext.tsx) automatically checks permissions:

```typescript
const userRole = getUserRole(session?.user?.email)
const canAccessQuestionBank = userRole === 'admin' || userRole === 'teacher'

// Only load data for authorized users
useEffect(() => {
  if (session?.user?.id && canAccessQuestionBank && !initialized) {
    initializeData()
  }
}, [session, canAccessQuestionBank, initialized])
```

## Navigation & UI

### Conditional Rendering
Components use role checks to show/hide features:

```typescript
{userRole === 'admin' && (
  <AdminPanel />
)}

{(userRole === 'admin' || userRole === 'teacher') && (
  <TeacherTools />
)}
```

### Route Protection
Pages check permissions and redirect unauthorized users:

```typescript
if (!hasPermission(session?.user?.email, 'canAccessAdmin')) {
  redirect('/dashboard')
}
```

